Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Russet Potato{12%oz} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{6%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Strip @Rosemary{¼%oz} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4). Halve, core, and cut @Apple{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes, carrots, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, chopped rosemary, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> Divide between 2 baking sheets for 4 servings; roast on top and middle racks.

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the pork and apple then).

While veggies roast, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper. Rub with a drizzle of oil.

> Swap in pork or beef for chicken; Once veggies have roasted for 12 minutes, add pork or beef to sheet. Roast until pork is cooked through, 15-20 minutes, or until beef reaches desired doneness, 12-15 minutes.

Once veggies have roasted 10 minutes, add chicken to same baking sheet. Carefully toss apple with veggies.

> For 4 servings, add chicken to one sheet and apple to other.

Return to top rack until veggies and apple are browned and tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{18-22%minutes}.

> For 4, return sheet with pork and veggies to top rack and sheet with veggies and apple to middle rack.

== Creamy Mustard ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @Honey{2%tsp}, and @Dijon Mustard{4%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Once chicken is done, carefully transfer to a #cutting board{}. Let rest at least ~{5%minutes}, then thinly slice crosswise.

> Love extra-crispy veggies? While chicken rests, heat broiler to high and return veggies to oven for 2-3 minutes more.

> Slice pork against the grain; chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Divide chicken and roasted veggies and apple between plates. Serve with creamy mustard on the side for dipping.